result.name: Cong Sao Star Dessert

reviews.text: Take a break w desserts.  Durian w pudding is fantastically rich and refreshing!  The hot walnut & sesame didnt disappoint too.  What a sweet break!

Delicious! At our table we had the mango+mango sherbet+grass jelly+sweet tofu, the mango+sago+coconut milk, and the fruit bowl thing. They were all delicious! I love sweet tofu so that one was definitely my favorite but the sago was also on point. I wish I could've had everything. It was so hard to decide. 

We went at 10:30 on a Friday. There was a wait to get in but the line moved quickly. They accommodated our party of six and were also pretty nice. Would come again.

I ordered the mango pomelo sago, which is listed on the menu as "sweet mango soup". I read that this place does it well. It was nice but I found it to be a bit too small for the price.

Later, a local told me to go to Chung Kee dessert, a 20 year old establishment. Ok, I don't usually slag off small businesses on Google maps but the following has to be said. At Chung kee, the mango pomelo sago was $33 and A LOT bigger and you could taste the pomelo. And it came with a scoop of ice cream. I'll post a review for the Sham Shui Po store.

Stuff on HK island is too damn expensive.

Ahhh these days so hard to find hot dessert stores in Causeway or wanchai.. so CS is a great find. Good quality and selection. My favourite almond and egg white.. but the latter ia not dropped into the hot almond oaste but already settled in. Else enjoyed the warm dessert just before sleep..

Slightly Higher end version of similar dessert places you can find around any corner, but better suited for tourists and first timers probably thanks to their large menus thus a way to try them all in one place. Worth it. Some options are vegan, just make sure with the staff.

reviews.text: 來香港🇭🇰必訪！榴蓮冰好吃😋。

マンゴーのアイスクリーム美味しすぎる！
同じようなデザートを提供するお店の中で一番シンプルで濃厚で美味しいです❤
量も他のお店のように多すぎず丁度良いです。
甘すぎるのが苦手で香港ではミルクティーなども砂糖なしでオーダーしますが、このマンゴーアイスは砂糖というよりマンゴーの濃厚な甘さなので罪悪感もなく全部ぺろっと食べられます✨
姐真的有個甜點的胃😘東西好吃～但諾要吃服務的不推薦～服務員有待加強😣～人超多～但不會等很久～

東西好吃卻抵不過服務態度的差勁！不只是對觀光客，連對自己香港人都是愛理不踩，點餐時不會靠近顧客桌邊，只會在櫃台外遠遠的看妳比菜單上的餐點，結單時結的品項跟我們吃的不一樣，找錢直接丟桌上，服務人員三個人全部都在看手機追劇，想點餐想結帳都叫不來。。。。。。。好可怕的一家店！
不想壞了遊興請三思！
寧願吃附近的“鮮芋仙”，冷氣又涼環境整潔！
東西說好吃也沒，但服務真的蠻差的倒是真的，很想只給一顆星....

result.name: Chung So Dessert

reviews.text: The 杨枝甘露 was nice, not too sweet and mango flavourful. Recommend to try the 龍眼椰果冰 at first might not be used to the unique taste and texture. But slowly you will find it's actually very good the coconut taste takes awhile to reach me.

Lovely local dessert! 
Not too sweet, fast service and delicious. Prices are on the higher side (~$50/dessert) and they request minimum 1 order per customer, cash only. 
Would recommend!
Tasty HK desserts with good portions but pricey.
Not so much choices than other dessert shops nearby, but overall quality and taste is better than the others.

The line to get in was a little long, but I'm sure there's a quieter time to go to this place. We went at night when the queue was pretty long, but the menu choices were pretty great and the desserts were delicious. I had the mango pudding.
